[Black "Foreword"]
[Result "*"]

1. --
{ Welcome to Thematic Tactics: Benko Gambit!   Learning an opening isn't just memorizing variations and understanding the general strategical ideas. In our opinion, you best amplify your knowledge in openings and structures by internalizing the common tactical motifs. This book gives you an overview of the most typical tactics in the Benko from both the White and the Black side. By learning them you will not only sometimes win a game effortlessly or stop a tactical idea from your opponent, you'll also strongly strengthen your understanding of positions arising from the Benko. If you try to understand why and when a certain tactic or sacrifice works, where the typically strong and weak points are and which pieces might be in danger, you will learn how to set up your pieces harmoniously.   Collecting the exercises for this course was especially enjoyable as the Benko offers a plethora of colorful tactics in all areas of the board. There are thematic chapters on tactics on the queenside, the center and kings attacks  (for both sides)  . Even in the endgame, you find typical motifs. There is also an entry chapter with simple puzzles, chapters for tactics on the a- and b-file, the diagonal a1-h8 and other diagonals. After these more than 100 exercises you can test your fresh skills in three test chapters of increasing average difficulty which consist of 30 positions each. Finally, there is a bonus chapter with extremely hard puzzles.   A few words on our approach to finding good and interesting positions. We've developed technology and sophisticated algorithms to automatically find correct and interesting puzzles for various topics. We handpick the best ones and refine the solutions. That means these puzzles are carefully selected by their relevance and cover all frequently occurring tactics. All puzzles have a clear and carefully checked solution.   Enjoy! }
*

