Nxe4
{ This is a common idea in Benoni-structures.   9...Qa5  looks just as strong since after 10. O-O Black still has 10... Nxe4, but White has  10.Nd2 !  when Black can only get a tiny edge with  Nxd5 !  11.Nxd5  Qxb5  12.Nxe7+  Kh8  13.Nxc8  Rxc8  14.Qe2 =  Black's position is a little more comfortable, but White should hold }
2. Nxe4 Qa5+ 3. Nc3 Bxc3+ 4. bxc3 Qxb5
{ Black won back his gambit pawn, White's king struggles to castle and White's pawn structure is bad. Black is clearly better. }
