Nxd5
{ A well known trick, but Black has to calculate relatively deep here.   1...Nxe4 ?  doesn't work instead. After  2.Bxe4  Bxc3+  3.bxc3  Qxc3+  White can defend with 4.Bd2 }
2. exd5 Bxc3+ 3. bxc3 Qxc3+ 4. Qd2 Qxa1 5. Ne2 Qg7
{ This retreat had to be spotted. Otherwise Black would face some serious problems along the a1-h8 diagonal. Now Black can simply block with f6 and enjoy his extra material }
