{ This chapter, together with the chapter on the a1-h8 diagonal, is probably the most important in this book. In most Benko games, even in some variations where White declines the gambit, Black will be getting serious pressure along the open a- and b-files. Knowing how to cash in on that pressure is one of the most valuable skills for any Benko player. }
