{ A little twist on this sacrifice. Black forces the queen to b2 in order to pin the c3-knight.   15...Bxc3  Giving away the fianchetto bishop for a pawn is often not worth it.  16.Bxc3  Qxa2  17.h3  Nge5  18.Nxe5  Nxe5  19.Bxe5  dxe5  20.d6  += }
2. Qxb2 Qxe2 3. Nxe2 Bxb2 4. Bc3 Bxc3
{ Black has his usual advantage after winning back the gambit pawn.  Not   18...Rxa2 ?  19.Rd2  Ndf6  20.Rxb2  Rxb2  21.Bxb2  Nxe4  =+  and Black has to fight for the draw. }
