{ This chapter illuminates White's main active idea in the Benko. While Black is trying to build pressure on the queenside with most of his pieces, he often has to leave his king under-protected. White often tries to cash in on this with a swift attack on the kingside. Typical attacking ideas are the e5-break, sacrifices on the light squares and pressure on the h-file. }
1. -- *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Kings Attack by White"]
[Black "Ageichenko, Genadi A(2350) vs. Meshkov, Yuri A(2285)"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "1rn2rk1/4ppbp/3p2p1/p1pPPqN1/PnQ5/1P3N2/3B1PPP/3RR1K1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Nxh7
{ The idea is analogous to the classical bishop sacrifice.   24.Qh4  is also winning, but White has to find a series of only moves  h6  25.g4 !  The only winning move  Qc2  26.Ne4 !  Qxb3  27.Bxh6 !  Bxh6  28.Qxh6  Qxf3  29.h3 !!  +-  Stopping Qxg4+. Now, Black is helpless against Ng5. }
1... Kxh7 2. Ng5+ Kg8 3. Qh4
{ White's attack is crushing. Play could continue with   26...Rd8  27.e6  f6  28.Qh7+  Kf8  29.Nf7  followed by Bh6 and a quick mate. }
*

