{ Transferring the queen this way wins.   24.Qh6 ?  allows Black to defend and even win. The point of the defence is hard to find though  Rf7  25.Reh1  Rxb2  26.Qg6+  Kf8   26...Rg7  27.Qxg7+  Kxg7  28.Rxh7+ =  is only a draw  27.Rxh7  Rxf2+ !!  28.Kxf2  Qd4+  and it's Black who mates !  29.Kg2  Qd2+  30.Kh3  Bd7+  31.g4  Rxh7+  32.Qxh7  Bxg4+  33.Kxg4  Qf4+  34.Kh3  Qg3# }
1... Rxb2
{ 24...Rf7  25.Nxa2  -+  Unpinning the c3-knight was another point of Qd1. } 2.
Qg4+ { and Black gets mated quickly.   25...Kf7  26.Rxh7+  Ke8  27.Qc8# } *

