1. e5
{ This breakthrough is often possible even if e5 looks fortified like here.   32.h4  is good as well, but not clearly winning as is the main line.  Nc7  33.h5  Qc2  34.hxg6  hxg6  35.Nh4  Kf7  36.f3  ±  White surely is better here, but there is a lot of work left to be done }
1... dxe5 2. Nxe5 { 33.Rxe5  Rb7  =+ } 2... Qxd5
{ 33...fxe5  34.Bxe5  Kf7  35.Qg7+  Ke8  36.Bd6  +- } 3. Nc6
{ Very nice, White ensures that his rook reaches e7 } 3... Qxc6
{ 34...e5  35.Ne7+  +- } 4. Rxe7 Rb7 5. Qg7# *

