{ White bravely castled to the queenside in this Benko game. Can you show that that wasn't a good idea ? }
1... e6
{ Opening the 7th rank for the f7-rook  Other moves are too slow.   18...Rff8  19.a3  Rfb8  20.Rde1 !  Kf8   20...Nd3+  21.Qxd3  Qxb2+  22.Kd1  -+  is nothing  21.Kd1  +-  and White's king escapes. Black's king however will be in huge trouble after the incoming f5. }
2. dxe6 { What else ? After other moves Black simply takes on d5. } 2... Rb7
{ Threatening Nxa2+. White has no sensible defense. } 3. a3 Nd3+
{ 20...d5  -+  wins as well } 4. Qxd3
{ 21.Kc2  loses material after  (Nxb2 -+) } 4... Qxb2# *

