c4 { Huh ? What is this about ? } 2. Bxc4
{ Retreating with the bishop with   14.Bb1  or   14.Bc2  leads to a similar position, but without an extra pawn. }
2... Qa7
{ This is the point. White can't prevent the Black queen from entering on f2. }
3. Qc2
{ 15.Rf1  stops Qf2, but leads to a sad position for White.  Nxh2  16.Rf2  Rc8  17.Qd3  Ng4  18.Rf1  -+  Black got his pawn back and with White's weak king and uncoordinated pieces his position is clearly for choice. }
3... Qf2+ { Black can simply take on g2 next move with a winning position. } *

