[SetUp "1"]

{ Black broke through on the queenside already, but White meanwhile put together a dangerous attack on the kingside. How should Black continue ? }
1... Rxf2+
{ Surprisingly it's not the Black, but the White king that is in grave danger.  Eliminating the dangerous knight on e3 with   27...Rc3  28.Rbe1   28.Nf5  Rxf2+  -+  is even worse now for White  28...Rxe3  29.Rxe3  Qc8  ∓  is clearly better for Black as well, but not nearly as convincing as the main line }
2. Kxf2 Qa2+ 3. Kf3 Nd7 4. Nc4
{ 30.Kg4  can be refuted by  Qe2+  31.Kh3   31.Kf5  Qf3+  32.Ke6  Nc5+  33.Kxe7  Qxe4+  34.Kxd6  Qe5#  31...Qxe3  -+  followed by Ne5 and an invasion along the c-file. The white king won't survive long here. Note how the white queen is out of play forever here.   30.Nf5  Ne5+  31.Ke3  Rc3+  32.Kd4  Rd3# }
4... Rxc4 { 30...Qc2  -+  is also good } 5. bxc4 Ne5+
{ 31...Qd2  -+  wins as well } 6. Ke3 { and finally } 6... Ng4+
{ winning the queen } *

