{ In this chapter we collected some very difficult puzzles. Some are probably even too difficult to solve from the starting position and intuition might be more important than calculation. When you tackle these positions, we advice you to set up a physical board, take your time and write down your thoughts. 30 minutes of calculation are the absolute minimum for some of these beasts. If you find these positions too difficult for solving, analyzing them with a friend or with an engine will surely be interesting. }
1. -- *

